Namasttay Shri Veeral Gandhi Ji and Everyone,

 

[veeralgandhi2011@... Sun 3/16/2014 2:50 PM:]

Your 'Why' and 'How' will lead you nowhere. It will only make you mad. Your
problem is your Western education background which encourages students to
always remain doubtful. 

Having faith in the words of great Acharyas does not make you dumb. Having
faith will give you a peace of mind.

[Kannnan:]

Those who do not ask questions are indeed dumb. Because they have shut-down
their critical capacity of thinking and pondering. I am an Achaarya, and I
always feel happy with those students who continuously keep asking me and
questioning me. I feel sad with those who never ask, and consider Achaarya's
words in blind faith. This is what has enslaved a majority of mankind by a
handful of evil people.

 

Faith obtained without proper questioning and satisfying one's intellect is
called Blind faith. Such Blind Faith is of no use to anyone, including
oneself. We must not exercise blind faith in any intellectual pursuits.
Faith is established not on a topic or subject or understanding, but on  the
person, after one's heart is thoroughly connected to him or her. But this is
a relationship, and we do not have relationship with everyone.

 

So I am very happy with Shri Phil Ji, as he has displayed the spirit of a
true learner, rarely seen among apes.

 

With Kind Regards,

Kannan

 

 

 

 


